article.description: Fifteen up, 15 down. Now the real season starts for Auburn (No. 10 ESPN/USA Today, No. 9 AP).
article.headline: Auburn outscores Stephen F. Austin in paint
article.linkText: Undefeated Auburn runs over Stephen F. Austin
article.story:
AUBURN, Ala. -- Fifteen up, 15 down. Now the real season starts for Auburn (No. 10 ESPN/USA Today, No. 9 AP).

Sherell Hobbs scored 19 points to lead the Tigers to a 79-56 win over Stephen F. Austin and send the Tigers into the SEC schedule undefeated.

DeWanna Bonner scored 17 points and Trevesha Jackson had 12 for Auburn (15-0), which outscored Stephen F. Austin 40-22 in the paint.

"I'm really pleased with finishing our non-conference schedule undefeated and taking that momentum to start the SEC season," Auburn coach Nell Fortner said. "We still have room for improvement and we still will improve."

The Tigers are off to their best start since winning their first 29 before losing to Tennessee late in the 1988-89 season. Auburn went on to win the SEC and reached the Final Four that season.

"I just have a lot of confidence in this team and the veterans," Fortner said of the four seniors in Auburn's starting lineup. "I've seen it all preseason long and it's something that just comes with experience."

Tammara Marion led the Ladyjacks (5-7) with 19 points.

The Tigers opened Saturday's game on a 14-0 run and took a 40-25 lead into halftime.

"We definitely have all the pieces," Bonner said. "We have chemistry and I think everything is there for us to be a great team in this league."
